Consider the following simple telescope configuration made up of thin lenses as follows:
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\mathrm{L}_{1}: f_{1}=10\,\mathrm{cm}, \text{ Diameter }=4\,\mathrm{cm} \\
\mathrm{L}_{2}: f_{2}=2\,\mathrm{cm}, D=1.2\,\mathrm{cm} \\ 
\mathrm{L}_{3}: f_{3}=2\,\mathrm{cm}, D=1.2\,\mathrm{cm}
\end{array}
$$
Calculate the position of the exit pupil and the diameter of the exit pupil.

Consider the following simple telescope configuration made up of thin lenses as follows:
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\mathrm{L}_{1}: f_{1}=10\,\mathrm{cm}, \text{ Diameter }=4\,\mathrm{cm} \\
\mathrm{L}_{2}: f_{2}=2\,\mathrm{cm}, D=1.2\,\mathrm{cm} \\
\mathrm{L}_{3}: f_{3}=2\,\mathrm{cm}, D=1.2\,\mathrm{cm}
\end{array}
$$
What is the function of the lens $\mathrm{L}_{2}$?
